name: Sang Natha SPICE MUSEUM
address: Jl. Gn. Batur No.28, Mengening, Kec. Kubutambahan, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81172, Indonesia
review 1:
It should be a nice and interesting place! When we arrived a guy showed up and explained about the location and the offer.

It's not like a museum where you just look at objects on display but rather they offer a guided tour through the whole process of making spices, including some tasting. This will take 2 hours and they charge 150k IDR per person.

Unfortunately, we didn't have that much time so we had to leave without a tour.
review 2: Planning to explore North of Bali? This museum of spices is a recommended place to get more insights about Indonesian local spices. To get there, you need to make a reservation first at the moment.
